723176f-a.text:
Seaman Avenue, north on west side from a little above Academy Street to the junction with 204th Street (known as Hawthorne Street prior to 1910). The newly erected apartment building is opposite the S.E. corner of 204th Street. The house in the foreground and the one just visible above the new building were both built around 1900.
October 26, 1927.

P. L. Speer.

715890f-a.text:
A rear view of No. 690 Academy Street, south side, east of Seaman Avenue. This is a 2 1/2- story frame house.
1932.

J. Clarence Davies Collection, Museum of the City of New York. Negative No. 438.
